GFO.title: Ground floor plan fully open (no walls)
GFO.name: GFO

H.title: Number of storeys above ground
H.desc:
H:n, exact number of storeys above ground.
H:a-b, range of storeys above ground.
H:<n, n upper limit of number of storeys above ground (with n excluded).
H:>n, n lower limit of number of storeys above ground (with n excluded).
H.name: H

HAPP.title: Approximate number of storeys above ground
HAPP.name: HAPP

HB.title: Number of storeys below ground
HB.desc:
Number of storeys below ground (same as number of basements).
HB:n, exact number of storeys below ground.
HB:a-b, range of storeys below ground.
HB:<n, n upper limit of number of storeys below ground (with n excluded).
HB:>n, n lower limit of number of storeys below ground (with n excluded).
HB.name: HB

HBAPP.title: Approximate number of storeys below ground
HBAPP.name: HBAPP

HD.title: Slope of the ground
HD.desc:
Slope of the ground (n=float in degrees).
HD:n
HD.name: HD

HF.title: Height of ground floor level above grade
HF.desc:
HF:n, exact height of ground floor above grade.
HF:a-b, range of height of ground floor above grade.
HF:<n, n upper limit of the height of ground floor above grade. (with n excluded).
HF:>n, n lower limit of the height of ground floor above grade. (with n excluded).
HF.name: HF

HFAPP.title: Approximate height of ground floor level above grade
HFAPP.name: HFAPP

HHI.title: Inter-storey height (average)
HHI.desc:
Float specifying the average floor height in meters. (HHI>= 1)
HHI:n
HHI.name: HHI

HHT.title: Total height of the structure, measured from the ground floor.
HHT.desc:
Total height of the structure, measured from the ground floor. Float specifying the height of the structures in meters. (HHT>= 1)
HHT:n
HHT.name: HHT

LDD.title: Different types of llrs in the two directions
LDD.name: LDD

LFC.title: Lateral load coefficient
LFC.desc: LFC:n, n is the lateral force coefficient in percentage (%)
LFC.name: LFC

LFLSINF.title: Infilled flat slab/plate or infilled waffle slab
LFLSINF.name: LFLSINF

LHV.title:
LHV(sys_a-sys_b), hybrid LLRS in height 
(a= primary system and secondary system)
LHV.name: LHV

MDD.title: Different materials in the two directions
MDD.name: MDD

PLFSQO.title: Square, with an interior opening (e.g. a "donut")
PLFSQO.name: PLFSQO

RTDP.title: Roof tie-down present (a connection that provides vertical attachment of roof to wall in order to restrain roof from upward displacement, lift-off due to wind)
RTDP.name: RTDP

RWCP.title: Roof-wall diaphragm connection present (the connection  transfers in-plane forces from floor to wall and restrains wall outward displacements)
RWCP.name: RWCP

WOL.title: Large openings (i.e. more than 50% of the wall surface area is occupied by windows and/or doors)
WOL.name: WOL

WOM.title: Moderate openings (i.e. from 20% to 50% of the wall surface area is occupied by windows and/or doors)
WOM.name: WOM

WOS.title: Small openings (i.e. less than 20% of the wall surface area is occupied by windows and/or doors)
WOS.name: WOS

Y.title: Date of construction or retrofit
Y.desc:
Y:n, exact date of construction or retrofit.
Y:a-b, range of date of construction or retrofit.
Y:<n, n upper limit of date of construction or retrofit (with n excluded).
Y:>n, n lower limit of date of construction or retrofit (with n excluded).
Y.name: Y

YAPP.title: Approximate date of construction or retrofit
YAPP.name: YAPP
